arch 1965\n| Moving On\n| Bill Mellen\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nBrian Parker (D)\n| \n|-\n| 31 March 1965\n| Cat's Cradle\n| Hugo Charteris\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nHenric Hirsch (D)\n| Recorded in the BBC's Glasgow studios\n|-\n| 7 April 1965\n| Three Clear Sundays\n| James O'Connor\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nKenneth Loach (D)\n| Repeated under 'Encore' on BBC2 16/07/1965.\n|-\n| 14 April 1965\n| The Interior Decorator\n| Jack Russell\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nJames Ferman (D)\n| \n|-\n| 21 April 1965\n| Auto-Stop\n| Alan Seymour\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nBrian Parker (D)\n| \n|-\n| 28 April 1965\n| The Good Shoemaker and the Poor Fish Peddler\n| Jean Benedetti\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nJohn Gorrie (D)\n| \n|-\n| 5 May 1965\n| Cemented with Love\n| Sam Thompson\n| Peter Luke (P)\nMichael Leeston-Smith (D)\n| Postponed from December 1964; shown in ''The Wednesday Play'' slot, although apparently not billed as such in the ''Radio Times'', according to the BBC Genome database.\n|-\n| 12 May 1965\n| A Knight in Tarnished Armour\n| Alan Sharp\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nJohn Gorrie (D)\n| \n|-\n| 26 May 1965\n| For the West\n| Michael Hastings\n| James McTaggart (P)\nToby Robertson (D)\n| \n|-\n| 2 June 1965\n| And Did Those Feet?\n| David Mercer\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nDon Taylor (D)\n| \n|-\n| 9 June 1965\n| The Man Without Papers\n| Troy Kennedy Martin\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nPeter Duguid (D)\n| \n|-\n| 16 June 1965\n| The Pistol\n| A novel by James Jones.\nAdapted for television by Troy Kennedy Martin and Roger Smith. \n| James MacTaggart (P)\nJames Ferman (D)\n| Repeated under 'Encore' on BBC2 10/09/1965.\n|-\n| 30 June 1965\n| The Seven O'Clock Crunch\n| David Stone\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nToby Robertson (D)\n| \n|-\n| 13 October 1965\n| Alice\n| Dennis Potter\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nGareth Davies (D)\n| \n|-\n| 20 October 1965\n| The Girl Who Loved Robots\n| Peter Everett\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nBrian Parker (D)\n| \n|-\n| 27 October 1965\n| A Designing Woman\n| Juli