ber 1968\n| The Lower Largo Sequence\n| Edward Boyd\n| Pharic MacLaren (P)\n| From Scotland\n|-\n| 16 October 1968\n| Hello, Good Evening, and Welcome\n| Hugh Whitemore\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nClaude Whatham (D)\n| \n|-\n| 30 October 1968\n| A Bit of Crucifixion, Father\n| Julia Jones\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nGeoffrey Nethercott (D)\n| \n|-\n| 6 November 1968\n| Nothing will be the Same Again\n| James Hanley\n| Irene Shubik (P)\nPeter Hammond (D)\n| \n|-\n| 20 November 1968\n| [[A Beast with Two Backs]]\n| Dennis Potter\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nLionel Harris (D)\n| \n|-\n| 27 November 1968\n| On the Eve of Publication\n| David Mercer\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nAlan Bridges (D)\n| Repeated also 06/12/1980 on BBC2, on 30/06/1988, and on 19&20/10/2002 on BBC4.\n|-\n| 8 January 1969\n| The Fabulous Frump\n| James Gibbins\n| Irene Shubik (P)\nPeter Hammond (D)\n| \n|-\n| 15 January 1969\n| Smoke Screen\n| Fay Weldon\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nDonald McWhinnie (D)\n| \n|-\n| 22 January 1969\n| Dr. Aitkinson's Daughter\n| Hugo Charteris\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nGilchrist Calder (D)\n| \n|-\n| 29 January 1969\n| The Apprentices\n| Peter Terson\n| \n| The National Youth Theatre production of The Apprentices\n|-\n| 12 February 1969\n| Birthday\n| Michael Frayn\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nClaude Whatham (D)\n| \n|-\n| 19 February 1969\n| [[The Big Flame]]\n| Jim Allen\n| Tony Garnett (P)\nKenneth Loach (D)\n| \n|-\n| 26 February 1969\n| A Serpent in Putney\n| Fred Watson\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nGeoffrey Nethercott (D)\n| \n|-\n| 5 March 1969\n| Bam! Pow! Zapp!\n| Nigel Kneale\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nWilliam Slater (D)\n| \n|-\n| 2 April 1969\n| Sling Your Hook\n| Roy Minton\n| Irene Shubik (P)\nMichael Tuchner (D)\n| \n|-\n| 9 April 1969\n| A Child and A Half\n| Owen Holder\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nAlan Bridges (D)\n| \n|-\n| 16 April 1969\n| [[Son of Man (play)|Son of Man]]\n| Dennis Potter\n| Graeme McDonald (P)\nGareth Davies (D)\n| Repeated also 28/07/1987, and 23/01/2005 on BBC4.\n|-\n